# Hound AI Test Automation Platform

## Project Overview
Hound is an AI-native test automation platform for authoring, running, and managing end-to-end tests using natural language and AI-powered steps.

## Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with TypeScript, App Router
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui components
- **Database**: Prisma ORM with SQLite (can migrate to PostgreSQL)
- **Authentication**: NextAuth.js with credentials provider
- **Browser Automation**: Playwright
- **AI Layer**: Anthropic Claude API (locator, assertion, failure agents)

## Project Structure
```
src/
  app/           # Next.js App Router
    (auth)/      # Login, Signup pages
    (dashboard)/ # Dashboard layout + project pages
    api/         # API routes (RESTful)
  components/    # React components (ui/, layout/)
  lib/           # Core libraries
    ai/          # AI agents (locator, assertion, failure)
    engine/      # Test execution engine
  types/         # TypeScript types
prisma/          # Database schema and migrations
```

## Step Types Supported (17 total)
1. `NAVIGATE` - Navigate to URL
2. `CLICK` - Click element
3. `TYPE` - Type text
4. `WAIT` - Wait for duration
5. `WAIT_FOR_URL` - Wait for URL change
6. `ASSERT_TEXT` - Assert text content
7. `ASSERT_ELEMENT` - Assert element presence
8. `ASSERT_VISUAL` - Visual regression
9. `AI_CHECK` - AI-powered assertion
10. `AI_EXTRACT` - AI-powered data extraction
11. `AI_ACTION` - AI-powered action
12. `JAVASCRIPT` - Execute JavaScript
13. `SCREENSHOT` - Capture screenshot
14. `HOVER` - Hover over element
15. `SELECT` - Select dropdown option
16. `PRESS_KEY` - Press keyboard key
17. `SCROLL` - Scroll page/element

## Implementation Phases
- **Phase 1**: Project Foundation (✅)
- **Phase 2**: Test Authoring (✅)
- **Phase 3**: Execution Engine (✅)
- **Phase 4**: AI Agent Layer (✅)
- **Phase 5**: Dashboard & Polish (Partial - remaining features)

## Phase 5 Remaining Features
1. **Test health indicators** - Pass rate, flakiness score, stability metrics
2. **Screenshot comparison** - Visual diff between runs
3. **Environment/variable management** - Multiple environments (dev/staging/prod)
4. **Bulk test operations** - Run/delete multiple tests at once

## Key Files
- `src/lib/engine/executor.ts` - Core test execution orchestrator
- `src/lib/engine/step-handlers.ts` - Step type implementations
- `src/lib/ai/` - AI agent implementations
- `prisma/schema.prisma` - Database schema
- `context.md` - Detailed project context
